commit.message:
Backport instances introduced in base-4.19

Fixes #68.

Backport instances introduced in base-4.18, fix up Down instances

The trickiest part was the `Down` instances, as:

* The `Bounded` and `Enum` instances have had their implementations change in
  `base` in the meantime.
* The `Integral` instance for `Down` has been removed entirely from `base`,
  and the vestigial `Integral` instance in `base-orphans` (which I had neglected
  to remove in the interim) now does not mix well with the new instance context
  for the `Enum` instance.

  As a result, I decided to rip off the bandage and remove the `Integral`
  instance from `base-orphans` as well. This requires a major version bump.

Fixes #64.

Fix unused import warnings with base-4.18.* (GHC 9.6)

`base-4.18.*` re-exports `liftA2` from the `Prelude`.

Only enable TypeInType on pre-8.6 GHCs

After GHC 8.6, `TypeInType`'s functionality was made a part of the `DataKinds`
and `PolyKinds` extensions. Moreover, GHC 9.6 gives a deprecation warning when
using `TypeInType`, so we now have an extra incentive to only enable
`TypeInType` where absolutely necessary.

Add missing backtick in CHANGELOG

[ci skip]

Backport Ix instances introduced in base-4.16.1.0

Fixes #60.

Make Ord1 Down instance use reverse sort order

This backports a change introduced in
https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/-/merge_requests/2158.

A part of a fix for #60.

Account for GHC#20371 in Data.Version.OrphansSpec

Fixes #61.

Synchronize Solo, Fixed instances with final GHC 9.2.1 release (#59)

This makes two additional GHC 9.2.1related changes:

* This backports `Eq`, `Ord`, `Bounded`, `Enum`, and `Ix` instances for
  `Solo`. See https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/-/merge_requests/6453.
* This removes the `Eq1` and `Ord1` instances for `Fixed`, which were
  ultimately removed from the final GHC 9.2.1 release. See
  https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/-/merge_requests/6454.

Fixes #58. Fixes #56 (hopefully for good this time).

commit.message:
Regenerate CI-related YAML files

This commit was performed automatically by a script.
https://github.com/RyanGlScott/ci-maintenance

Migrate from Travis CI to GitHub Actions

Travis CI recently announced
[changes to its pricing model](https://blog.travis-ci.com/2020-11-02-travis-ci-new-billing)
that will affect OSS projects. Whereas Travis previously allowed unrestricted
hours for OSS projects to run on their build machines, the new pricing model
will require the use of credits, of which free plans only have a limited
quantity. Moreover, Travis now takes an extraordinarily long time to actually
serve CI requests, which is infeasible in the long term.

As a result, I have decided
(with encouragement from other Haskell maintainers, see
[here](https://old.reddit.com/r/haskell/comments/jvbs49/psa_maintainers_should_think_about_migrating_off/))
to migrate to GitHub Actions. This
relies on a very recent version of `haskell-ci` that features a GitHub Actions
backend.
